    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-05-28T19:14:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-05-28T19:14:00-05:00" n="368"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d368">
                <head>368. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Canada</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d368fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 442.4841/5–2857. Official Use Only. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_GHM1">Howard M. Gabbert</persName> and
                            <persName>John</persName> M. Leddy; cleared with <gloss target="#t_ITR1"
                            >ITR</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_BNA1">BNA</gloss>, E, and W; approved
                        and signed for <persName>Dulles</persName> by Leddy.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1957-05-28T20:14:00-04:00">May 28, 1957— 8:14 p.m.</date>
                        </hi>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>442. Hope conclude Polish agreement<note n="2" xml:id="d368fn2">An agreement with
                        Poland was reached on June 7. For text, see Department of State <hi
                            rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, June 24, 1957, pp. 1005–1008.</note> late
                    this week or early next week to provide: <list>
                        <label>a.</label>
                        <item>Eximbank component including about 100,000 MT wheat effective
                            immediately.</item>
                        <label>b.</label>
                        <item>Interim Title I no wheat effective immediately.</item>
                        <label>c.</label>
                        <item>Subject to advance consultation with appropriate members of Congress
                            additional Title I including about 400,000 MT wheat to become effective
                            when Congress passes <gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss>–480
                            legislation.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Every possible effort made persuade Poles satisfy Canadian desires. Poles have
                    given general assurance US wheat will not displace Canadian sales but state
                    emphatically cannot make definite advance commitment to Canadians, especially in
                    view problem this would create re other countries. <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                        >Dept</gloss> considers US has fully carried out undertaking given to
                    Canadians. Canadian Embassy (Ritchie) informed by <persName corresp="#p_KTV1"
                        >Kalijarvi</persName> today.<note n="3" xml:id="d368fn3">No record of a
                        conversation between Ritchie and <persName corresp="#p_KTV1"
                            >Kalijarvi</persName> has been found in Department of State
                        files.</note> Informing <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
